A bird in hand is worth more than a hundred flying around']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131895585.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A classic Spanish saying, 'A bird in the hand is worth more than a hundred flying,' highlights the importance of appreciating what you have rather than chasing uncertain prospects. This proverb serves as a universal reminder that we often prioritize security over risk, a concept supported by behavioral economics. It's a vital lesson for making sound choices in finance, career paths, and everyday life.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/spanish-proverb-of-the-day-a-bird-in-hand-is-worth-more-than-a-hundred-flying-around-and-why-certainty-often-beats-risky-rewards/articleshow/131895585.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/spanish-proverb-of-the-day-a-bird-in-hand-is-worth-more-than-a-hundred-flying-around-and-why-certainty-often-beats-risky-rewards/articleshow/131895585.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T23:35:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131895743,imgsize-101304.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Heat dome over Europe brings travel chaos, health alerts and wildlife stress]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131895501.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Europe is grappling with a severe heatwave, with temperatures soaring towards 40°C, triggering health alerts and transport chaos. Italy has issued red alerts for eight cities, while France faces significant rail disruptions. Wildlife is also under immense pressure. Experts link these extreme conditions to climate change, with concerns growing over prolonged heat and its impact on public safety and infrastructure across the continent.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/heat-dome-over-europe-brings-travel-chaos-health-alerts-and-wildlife-stress/articleshow/131895501.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/heat-dome-over-europe-brings-travel-chaos-health-alerts-and-wildlife-stress/articleshow/131895501.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T23:24:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131895559,imgsize-143319.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Melinda French Gates: "Shaming women for their sexuality is a standard tactic for…"]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131895427.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-melinda-french-gates-shaming-women-for-their-sexuality-is-a-standard-tactic-for/articleshow/131895427.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-melinda-french-gates-shaming-women-for-their-sexuality-is-a-standard-tactic-for/articleshow/131895427.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-22T00:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131895434,imgsize-1701059.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Portuguese proverb of the day: 'One day belongs to the prey, another to the hunter']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131895244.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The age-old Portuguese saying, "One day belongs to the prey, another to the hunter," encapsulates the unpredictable nature of life. This proverb serves as a poignant reminder that success and failure are fleeting. It calls for humility in triumph and instills hope in defeat, demonstrating that today's champions can easily falter tomorrow, whether in sports, business, or personal endeavors.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/portuguese-proverb-of-the-day-one-day-belongs-to-the-prey-another-to-the-hunter-and-the-reminder-that-fortunes-can-change-without-warning/articleshow/131895244.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/portuguese-proverb-of-the-day-one-day-belongs-to-the-prey-another-to-the-hunter-and-the-reminder-that-fortunes-can-change-without-warning/articleshow/131895244.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T23:20:46+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131895421,imgsize-195784.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[NY boy finds mom’s dead body with throat slit; ‘someone followed her home,’ says husband]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131894064.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/new-york-boy-finds-moms-dead-body-with-throat-slit-someone-followed-her-home-says-husband/articleshow/131894064.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/new-york-boy-finds-moms-dead-body-with-throat-slit-someone-followed-her-home-says-husband/articleshow/131894064.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T22:30:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131894303,imgsize-220764.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How China is using maritime tactics and propaganda to squeeze Taiwan]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131894063.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Taiwan's security official warns China is increasingly using 'grey-zone' tactics like coast guard patrols and legal claims to pressure the island, moving away from direct military threats. Beijing is exploiting international law and maritime activities to advance its objectives, while Taiwan is urged to adopt 'absolute transparency' and enhance regional cooperation to counter these evolving challenges amidst ongoing Chinese military drills.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/how-china-is-using-maritime-tactics-and-propaganda-to-squeeze-taiwan/articleshow/131894063.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/how-china-is-using-maritime-tactics-and-propaganda-to-squeeze-taiwan/articleshow/131894063.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T22:11:58+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131894114,imgsize-394475.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Former USSR leader's great-grandson captured by Ukraine: Reports]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131893356.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Reports indicate Anton Milaev, adopted great-grandson of Leonid Brezhnev, has been captured by Ukrainian forces. Milaev, reportedly a sapper, was last heard from in November 2025. Ukrainian military intelligence and prisoner of war coordination sources have allegedly confirmed his custody in the Kherson region. His presence on a Ukrainian 'enemies' database has also been noted. The circumstances of his capture and potential for exchange remain unclear amidst ongoing conflict.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/former-ussr-leader-leonid-brezhnevs-great-grandson-captured-by-ukrainian-forces-while-fighting-for-russia-reports/articleshow/131893356.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/former-ussr-leader-leonid-brezhnevs-great-grandson-captured-by-ukrainian-forces-while-fighting-for-russia-reports/articleshow/131893356.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T21:11:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131893459,imgsize-935581.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Napoleon Bonaparte: "The only victories which leave no regret are…" - the surprising belief of history's most famous conqueror]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131893167.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-napoleon-bonaparte-the-only-victories-which-leave-no-regret-are-the-surprising-belief-of-historys-most-famous-conqueror/articleshow/131893167.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-napoleon-bonaparte-the-only-victories-which-leave-no-regret-are-the-surprising-belief-of-historys-most-famous-conqueror/articleshow/131893167.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-21T20:51:09+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131893205,imgsize-92379.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Keir Starmer will resign': Donald Trump makes bold claim, accuses UK PM of 'failing badly' on 2 subjects]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left